 In an evaluation over correctness of inferred negations [arnaout020enriching], this simple yet powerful rule increases the accuracy of results by 27%. Remaining candidate negations are finally scored by relative peer frequency. For instance, 2 out of 2 peers of Hawking have won the Nobel Prize in Physics but only 1 out of 2 is the parent of Eduard Einstein.